Iavan Pijoos, News24 Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Durban &ndash; A 40-year-old man was arrested for human trafficking, abduction, rape and violating the Immigration Act, after he allegedly abducted three children, the Hawks said.The Swaziland national allegedly abducted three children aged 5, 7 and 13 in Swaziland last year, Captain Simphiwe Mhlongo said.A case was opened at Mbabane and the docket was handled by Interpol.&nbsp;Mhlongo said while he was in South Africa he allegedly repeatedly raped and impregnated the 13-year-old girl.The children were rescued last week and put in a place of safety.&nbsp;He would appear in the Durban Regional Court on Friday.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.